            <p class="tdg-boxtext"><strong>White to move, mate in 2.</strong> A fresh tactic to sharpen your eye before your coffee gets cold.</p>
            <details class="tdg-solution">
              <summary>Show solution</summary>
              <p class="tdg-soltext">1. Rc8+ Bd8 (or 1… Bf8) 2. Rxd8# (2. Rxf8#) — the rook check forces the bishop to block on the back rank, and capturing it delivers mate with the black king boxed in by its own pawns.</p>
              <p class="tdg-solnote">Theme: Mate in 2 · from the <a href="/chess-school/tactics">Tactics Trainer</a>.</p>
            </details>
